description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advert: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Programme Manager &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: AfC 8B&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We seek an experienced, passionate and organised leader to join the digital innovation team at NHSX as a Programme Manager on a fixed term basis until 31 March 2021. This team focuses on working with partners across the NHS and social care and digital health innovators to help accelerate the digital transformation of health and care. Please note the reason for the fixed term of your contract is due to the second wave of Covid-19 there is a need for us to accelerate the scale of programmes and as such we are looking to bring in people who can support this ASAP&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHSX exists to make sure that patients and staff have the digital technology they need and this is a key role in our crucial mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post holder will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee aspects of a programme of implementation of digital health across the health and care sector for Outpatients and Long-Term Conditions related programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the design and delivery of a programme that will prioritise innovations that make the most difference and accelerate partners for implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that rigorous project management, benefits realisation and a communications strategy are embedded in this programme to ensure the work is recognised nationally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain links with health and care stakeholders and patient groups nationally to consistently ensure that feedback improves the work that we do&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with other departments across NHS England and NHS and Social Care bodies to co-ordinate activities across teams and provide a cohesive programme of activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outline and promote the mission and objectives of NHSX and their activities in enhancing the performance of the NHS through greater adoption of technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role supports the business in driving transformation as well as value for money in planning, commissioning and service. The role is designed to build a combination of subject matter expertise and technical skills to develop a strong service delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The digital innovation team is a great new team focused on the interface between health, social care and digital innovation and speeding up the scaling of the strongest solutions with the biggest benefits to citizens and staff in NHS and social care. Your experience in driving forward projects will play a vital role in supporting a range of high priority programmes currently being delivered by the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All roles are currently home based due to the impact of COVID-19. This role is nominally based at our London HQ which is located in Elephant and Castle and may require a small amount of travel both to our Leeds HQ and across the country as we work very collaboratively with partners, so the post-holder will need to be happy to work in a mobile capacity as well as from home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report to our Director of Innovation Delivery, Lisa Hollins. Working closely, where appropriate, with many other teams across NHSX and with our partners at NHS&amp;I and NHS Digital. Shortlisted candidates will be invited to attend a virtual panel interview. The closing date for applications is Sunday 8th November 2020 at midnight. Interviews will be held in early November.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are happy to accept applications from candidates looking for full time and part time posts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name - Yinka Makinde&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title - Head of Innovation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address - yinka.makinde@nhsx.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
